. Long before John Lennon testified at Canada’s Le Dain Commission in favour of marijuana decriminalization, social movements existed to challenge the view that consumption of mind-altering substances, especially by young people, posed a danger to society. The contributors to this collection explore how drugs and alcohol intersect with diverse histories, including gender, medicine, popular culture, and business. Pleasure and Panic brings a dispassionate voice to current debates about liberalizing drug and alcohol laws and challenges existing ideas about how to deal with the so-called problems of drug and alcohol use.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDrugs of abusezCanadaxHistory. 0aDrugs of abusezUnited StatesxHistory. 0aHarm reduction. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh1 aBelaskie, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBellamy, Matthew J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElcock, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFillion, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamill, Sarah E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrasnick Warsh, Cheryl, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLafferty-Salhany, Renée, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalleck, Dan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalleck, Dan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMarquis, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReinarz, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarsh, Cheryl Krasnick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook pack